<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Emissions_trading&amp;action=edit&amp;section=23" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<p><a name="General_trading" id="General_trading"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Emissions_trading&amp;action=edit&amp;section=24" title="Edit section: General trading">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">General trading</span></h3>
<ul>
<li>Chemical Engineering Topics<a href="http://www.newseminar.co.cc" class="external text" title="http://www.newseminar.co.cc" rel="nofollow">Chemical Engineering Topics</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.nature.com/news/2004/041115/pf/432268a_pf.html" class="external text" title="http://www.nature.com/news/2004/041115/pf/432268a_pf.html" rel="nofollow">Emissions trading: The carbon game news@nature.com Nov. 17, 2004</a></li>
<li><a href="http://business.guardian.co.uk/comment/story/0,,1975207,00.html" class="external text" title="http://business.guardian.co.uk/comment/story/0,,1975207,00.html" rel="nofollow">Ministers know emissions trading is a red herring and won't work, by George Monbiot, The Guardian, December 19, 2006</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.epa.gov/airmarkets/progsregs/arp/index.html" class="external text" title="http://www.epa.gov/airmarkets/progsregs/arp/index.html" rel="nofollow">US EPA's Acid Rain Program</a></li>
